original: Behm, Olof Albrekt, tandläkare, Kungsbacka, f. 12/3/96 i Hälsingborg av lektor Olof Pedro B. o. Märta Zet- terström. G. 21 m. Elsie Sonesson. Barn: Brita f. 22, g. 46 m. musikdir. Lennart Svegelius, Kungsbacka, Lars 24, Gudrun 28. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 14, res loff :ex. 16, tandl:kand. 18, tandl. 20. Fänrik i Göta art:reg. res. 16, undilöjtn. där 19, avsk. 21. Prakt, i Kungsbacka sed. 20, skoltandl. där 20-32. Sekr. i Halil. tandl :fören. 30-31, led. av stadsfullm. 31-42, v. ordf. i styr. f. komm. mellansk., led. av fat-tigvistyr., huv :man o. styrrled. i Fjä-re Härads Sparbank. Skr.: art. o. föredr. i skoltandv :frågor.
translated: Behm, Olof Albrekt, dentist, Kungsbacka, born March 12, 1896 in Helsingborg to lecturer Olof Pedro B. and Märta Zetterström. Married in 1921 to Elsie Sonesson. Children: Brita born in 1922, married in 1946 to music director Lennart Svegelius from Kungsbacka, Lars born in 1924, Gudrun born in 1928. Completed high school in Latin in Gothenburg in 1914, reserved officer exam in 1916, dental studies completed in 1918, became a licensed dentist in 1920. Became a second lieutenant in the Göta Artillery Regiment in 1916 and a lieutenant in 1919 before leaving military service in 1921. Started practicing dentistry in Kungsbacka in 1920 and worked as a school dentist there from 1920 to 1932. Served as secretary in the Halland dental association from 1930 to 1931, member of the city council from 1931 to 1942 and vice chairman of the committee for municipal intermediates. Also served as a member of the poor relief board and as head and board member of the Fjäre Härads Savings bank. Wrote articles and gave lectures on school dental issues.

structured.name: Olof Albrekt Behm
structured.description: Olof Albrekt Behm was a dentist from Kungsbacka, Sweden. He was born on March 12, 1896 in Helsingborg to lecturer Olof Pedro B. and Märta Zetterström. He completed high school in Latin in Gothenburg in 1914, reserved officer exam in 1916, dental studies completed in 1918, and became a licensed dentist in 1920. He served as a second lieutenant in the Göta Artillery Regiment from 1916-1921 and started practicing dentistry in Kungsbacka in 1920. He also worked as a school dentist in Kungsbacka from 1920 to 1932. Behm was involved in various organizations throughout his life, including the Halland Dental Association, City Council, Fjäre Härads Savings bank, Municipal Intermediates Committee, and Poor Relief Board. He wrote articles and gave lectures on school dental issues.
